104// PeerConnection is the implementation of the PeerConnection object as defined
105// by the PeerConnectionInterface API surface.
106// The class currently is solely responsible for the following:
107// - Managing the session state machine (signaling state).
108// - Creating and initializing lower-level objects, like PortAllocator and
109// BaseChannels.
110// - Owning and managing the life cycle of the RtpSender/RtpReceiver and track
111// objects.
112// - Tracking the current and pending local/remote session descriptions.
113// The class currently is jointly responsible for the following:
114// - Parsing and interpreting SDP.
115// - Generating offers and answers based on the current state.
116// - The ICE state machine.
117// - Generating stats.
118class PeerConnection : public PeerConnectionInternal,
119 public JsepTransportController::Observer,
120 public sigslot::has_slots<> {
121 public:
122 // Creates a PeerConnection and initializes it with the given values.
123 // If the initialization fails, the function releases the PeerConnection
124 // and returns nullptr.
125 //
126 // Note that the function takes ownership of dependencies, and will
127 // either use them or release them, whether it succeeds or fails.
128 static RTCErrorOr<rtc::scoped_refptr<PeerConnection>> Create(
129 rtc::scoped_refptr<ConnectionContext> context,
130 const PeerConnectionFactoryInterface::Options& options,
131 std::unique_ptr<RtcEventLog> event_log,
132 std::unique_ptr<Call> call,
133 const PeerConnectionInterface::RTCConfiguration& configuration,
134 PeerConnectionDependencies dependencies);
